Happiest 30th Birthday to the best, sweetest @KAY_T_LIM , my cousin 💜 your impressive fearlessness and deeply committed love to our family has us on the trip of a lifetime that I will never forget. You deserve to be the happiest 24/7 365 and ♾ 

🎈🎈🎈🎈🎈
cousin drip 💧

this is for my family ♥️ 

i have always felt most at home with my dad's side of the family  - they raised me alongside my mom and dad from day 1. summer and winter short term stays with my Nai Nai and Yeh Yeh in Jackson Heights, Queens, NYC profoundly shaped my definition of what family means and how to love and be loved by someone.

this is my first time stepping foot on the continent of Asia. for as long as i've had memory, i have wanted to visit Cambodia. it has become the enigmatic mythical hero in a chapter of my family's history that is of paramount importance to our lineage story. i've asked my dad ad nauseum to tell me stories of his time growing up there - i clung to anything he would be willing to share, glossing his sometimes reluctant re-tellings in wonder when i didn't have enough details to fully bring our family story to life in color. the khmer rouge had a lasting impact on my family and all Cambodian families in that way. 

years passed, our lives developed and my 20s were filled with a range of life experiences for which i am grateful, yet still - no visit to Cambodia. 

my cousin Kayleen and i decided rather suddenly (that’s another story for later) this fall that we would travel to Cambodia for her 30th birthday and the trip evolved effortlessly from there.

a lot has happened over the last month as Kayleen and i traveled through cambodia, vietnam, back to cambodia, to malaysia and now singapore.

i haven’t decided how much i’ll share here yet, but what i do know i want to share now is how deeply touched i am by this experience. our trip has been defined by the selflessness, humility, grace, bravery and overwhelmingly joyful demeanour of our uncle david and aunt kheng. without their guidance and vulnerability, i would never know the family that still lives here in this graciously beautiful country, nor would i know the love they have for Kayleen and i. i've cried so much on this trip i didn't know i had this many tears inside of me. i am so grateful for this, i’m forever in gratitude to @kay_t_lim for walking next to me through this. it is the most precious gift of all to have been born on this day into this family.

♥️
